==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bottlehead
<hw>Bot"tle*head`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A cetacean allied to the grampus; -- called also
<altname>bottle-nosed whale</altname><-- bottle-nosed dolphin?
-->.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are several species so named, as the pilot whales,
of the genus <gen>Globicephalus</gen>, and one or more species of
<gen>Hypero⟦oum⟧don</gen> (<spn>Hypero⟦oum⟧don bidens</spn>, etc.),
found on the European coast. See <er>Blackfish</er>, 1.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bottleholder</ent>⟦br⟧
